properties.areaDesc: Southern Oconto County; Manitowoc; Door; Southern Marinette County; Brown; Kewaunee
properties.headline: Lakeshore Flood Advisory issued January 10 at 3:26PM CST until January 12 at 3:00AM CST by NWS Green Bay WI
properties.description:
The National Weather Service in Green Bay has issued a Lakeshore
Flood Advisory, which is in effect from 10 PM this evening to
3 AM CST Sunday.

* LOCATIONS...Shorelines of Marinette, Oconto, Brown, Door,
Kewaunee and Manitowoc counties.

* LAKESHORE FLOODING...Strong northeast winds may cause water to
back up on rivers that flow into the bay, leading to lakeshore
flooding. High waves on Lake Michigan may cause shoreline
erosion and localized flooding.

* TIMING...10 pm this evening through 3 am Sunday.

* IMPACTS...Flooding is possible in lowland areas near the bay,
including the Fox and East Rivers in Green Bay. Flooding and
erosion is also possible along the Lake Michigan shoreline. Ice
shoves could also occur on the southern end of the bay.
properties.instruction:
A Lakeshore Flood Advisory indicates that onshore winds will
generate flooding of low areas along the lakeshore.

NWSheadline: LAKESHORE FLOOD ADVISORY IN EFFECT FROM 10 PM THIS EVENING TO 3 AM CST SUNDAY
